		<hr />
		
		
		
		
		<div>As much as I hate religion and would like it to go away with theories like these, I think this theory can't explain everything away. Schizophrenic people are not like they are portrayed in movies or books. Most schizophrenics who have some form of hallucinations typically have the auditory variety. That would explain away the hearing of voices from god. However Jesus, Mohammed, and others also reported visual apparitions. Those are extremely rare in the case of schizophrenia due to the parts of the brain that are typically shown to be affected. In almost all cases, the temporal lobe and the thalamus are most affected by schizophrenia. To explain the visual hallucinations, something would have to be going on in the occipital lobe of everyone who reported seeing angels and such. That is just too unlikely. <br />
<br />
Now, I am not saying that visual hallucinations are not a symptom of schizophrenia because it has been said to accompany the disease in very rare cases, even olfactory hallucinations could theoretically occur. I am just saying that the likelihood of a mass spread of schizophrenia. <br />
<br />
Schizophrenia is a strange disease that isn't very well understood right now. Unfortunately, it is also used as a catch all in the psychology world for a broad range of symptoms. Hallucinations are just part of what are called the &quot;positive&quot; symptoms used to classify schizophrenia in the DSM manual. Positive symptoms are things that a person is almost thought to have extra that they shouldn't have. They include: hallucinations, delusions, catatonia, disorganized behavior, and strange speech. That doesn't even include the &quot;negative&quot; symptoms! Negative symptoms include: poor memory, slow speech, slow thinking, poor concentration, difficulty with expression. <br />
<br />
The thing about all the symptoms is that a schizophrenic person almost never just has positive symptoms without having some negative symptoms. Think about all those symptoms and tell me how many Jesus and Mohammed have been descibed as having. Then look at everyone else in the Bible and see which they display.<br />
<br />
In short, a very unlikely theory...</div>
	</td>
</tr>
